choices.label: Meat Eater - This includes all red meat, eggs and poultry.
Vegetarian - A person who does not eat any animal products, poultry, fish or seafood. Includes: Lacto-ovo (eats eggs & dairy), Lacto (eats dairy), Ovo (eats eggs), Pollo vegetarians (eats poultry).
Vegan - A person who excludes all animal products including honey, and eggs as well as poultry, fish, dairy and seafood.
Pescatarian - A person who does not eat meat or poultry but eats fish and seafood.
Fodmap - Stands for fermentable oligosaccharides, disaccharides, monosaccharides and polyols.
